parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause sudden loss of power, unexpected acceleration, or complete loss of transmission function, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Poor acceleration can lead to accidents, especially when merging onto highways or crossing intersections.
symptoms: Very poor acceleration when taking off from a complete stop
similar symptoms to a previous recall for the 2015-2016 Outlander Sport.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to die frequently, turn off while driving, or experience other unexpected electrical issues.
symptoms: battery replacement does not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: the electrical components won't shut off
and the power locks are inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ETACS (Electronic Time and Alarm Control System) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETACS can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: The low beam and high beams go out simultaneously
the headlights do not turn on
and the vehicle's electrical system may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Illumination of Multiple Dashboard Warning Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained illumination of multiple dashboard warning lights can cause confusion and distraction, potentially leading to accidents or other safety issues on the road.
symptoms: illuminate simultaneously while the vehicle is stationary or in motion
with no apparent cause or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning FCM system can fail to alert the driver of potential collisions, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The FCM warning light illuminates intermittently or remains on
even when there is no apparent obstacle or hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty LDW system can fail to alert the driver of unintentional lane drift, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: even when the vehicle is not drifting out of its lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning AHB system can reduce visibility and increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: even when the headlights are functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty ASC system can fail to provide critical safety features, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: even when the vehicle is operating normally.
